-- France Rallies in Doubles to Take 2-1 Lead Over Serbia in Davis Cup Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-12-04T18:53:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-04/france-rallies-in-doubles-to-take-2-1-lead-over-serbia-in-davis-cup-final.html
Arnaud Clement and Michael Llodra
rallied to defeat Nenad Zimonjic and Viktor Troicki in five sets
to give France a 2-1 lead over Serbia in the Davis Cup tennis
final.  Clement and Llodra won 3-6, 6-7 (3-7), 6-4, 7-5, 6-4 in
Belgrade to move within one more victory of its 10th Davis Cup
title overall and first since 2001. Serbia is playing in the
final for the first time.  Serbia’s Novak Djokovic is scheduled to play Gael Monfils
in tomorrow’s first reverse singles match, followed by Janko
Tipsarevic taking on France’s Giles Simon.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  